Equations
You can create equations using the $$ symbol. For example in Equation 1, we have the formula for the standard deviation of a population:
$$
\sigma = \sqrt{\frac{\sum_{i=1}^{N} (x_i - \mu)^2}{N}}
$$ {#eq-stddev}
\[
\sigma = \sqrt{\frac{\sum_{i=1}^{N} (x_i - \mu)^2}{N}}
\tag{1}\]
You can also create equations inline by using the $ symbol. For example, $\alpha = \beta + \gamma$ will render as \(\alpha = \beta + \gamma\). To learn more about how to write equations in using Markdown, you can refer to the Overleaf documentation.
